climbs.name: Kill Them All and Let God Sort Them Out
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Tucker Tech, Kelby Burnham, Tom Burke, Chris Gorsky

content.description: This is on the lower black buttress. Begin in a crack and move left onto buttress and climb up past maybe 6 or so bolts.
content.protection: QDs for the bolts, and maybe a piece or two to supplement the bolts.
content.location: On the lower black buttress of the east east of a long wall which is way up to the SW of the Corral Wall, and easily seen from the Corral Wall.

content.description: This is a cool, right facing dihedral. This climb starts on a high tier, above a black buttress. This is the best of the climbs in this area, and was done a number of years ago by an unknown party.
content.protection: trad gear, mostly thin to med.
content.location: On the East end of a long wall up ans SW of the Corral Wall, easily seen from the Corral Wall.
